1
00:00:16,266 --> 00:00:18,225
[NOREEN] Your ball is all set, Miss V.

2
00:00:18,226 --> 00:00:19,978
[VELMA] We must act fast, Noreen.

3
00:00:20,719 --> 00:00:21,720
Tell us the plan.

4
00:00:22,930 --> 00:00:24,932
I've already woken up to the truth, Eddie.

5
00:00:26,934 --> 00:00:28,978
[NOREEN] You will die during your ball, Miss Velma.

6
00:00:29,144 --> 00:00:30,145
A fake death.

7
00:00:31,730 --> 00:00:34,107
[MIGOY] You need to disappear that night, Miss Velma,

8
00:00:34,108 --> 00:00:36,485
so he can’t have you arrested.

9
00:00:36,944 --> 00:00:38,404
That way, Eddie will end up getting arrested.

10
00:00:38,862 --> 00:00:40,364
We’re not going to let Eddie take the fall.

11
00:00:41,156 --> 00:00:42,241
It’ll be you, Shari.

12
00:00:43,117 --> 00:00:43,784
Really, Noreen?

13
00:00:43,785 --> 00:00:45,869
I really can't stay there for long.

14
00:00:46,036 --> 00:00:47,662
[EDDIE] "Waking up to the truth"?
What truth?!

15
00:00:47,663 --> 00:00:50,331
The truth that I loved a heartless monster!

16
00:00:50,332 --> 00:00:52,292
You drugged her! You raped her!

17
00:00:52,626 --> 00:00:53,669
You killed her!

18
00:00:54,044 --> 00:00:56,045
You murdered her! You're a murderer!

19
00:00:56,046 --> 00:00:57,006
That's enough!

20
00:00:57,339 --> 00:00:59,174
[NOREEN] He’s completely fallen for my trap.

21
00:00:59,258 --> 00:01:00,759
[EDDIE] You're going to stab me in the chest?

22
00:01:01,010 --> 00:01:02,302
Before you get the
chance to do that,

23
00:01:02,386 --> 00:01:03,178
[VELMA GASPS]

24
00:01:03,387 --> 00:01:05,014
I will kill you first.

25
00:01:05,055 --> 00:01:08,434
I’ve convinced him we’re allies.

26
00:01:10,227 --> 00:01:11,979
Did you capture everything?

27
00:01:13,063 --> 00:01:13,897
Everything.

28
00:01:15,149 --> 00:01:16,525
Is everything set?

29
00:01:21,864 --> 00:01:24,158
I’ve got everything ready...

30
00:01:24,742 --> 00:01:25,868
There's just one thing missing.

31
00:01:31,999 --> 00:01:39,256
[GANDA GANDAHAN BY DIA MATÉ PLAYING]

32
00:02:22,132 --> 00:02:23,008
[VELMA SIGHS IN RELIEF]

33
00:02:27,429 --> 00:02:29,056
Thank God you guys are finally here.

34
00:02:31,183 --> 00:02:32,059
Was there a problem?

35
00:02:34,186 --> 00:02:36,688
We just had to make sure no one saw us.

36
00:02:37,439 --> 00:02:39,566
Jana managed to bring everything safely.

37
00:02:40,150 --> 00:02:41,443
I’ve got everything you need.

38
00:02:42,111 --> 00:02:42,986
Thank you, Jana.

39
00:02:43,654 --> 00:02:44,613
What about the main switch?

40
00:02:45,030 --> 00:02:46,073
I’ll handle it.

41
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,658
I'll keep watch outside.

42
00:02:54,039 --> 00:02:55,624
Let’s get this show started.

43
00:02:56,500 --> 00:02:58,418
I can’t wait.

44
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:11,807
Don’t worry, Shari.

45
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:14,643
We’ll get you out of this.

46
00:03:16,228 --> 00:03:17,729
I'll make sure of that.

47
00:03:24,987 --> 00:03:30,492
We just need to make it look like you
killed me so Eddie can’t escape.

48
00:03:32,911 --> 00:03:35,497
And once the evidence
against him comes to light,

49
00:03:36,081 --> 00:03:37,583
he’ll be the one arrested.

50
00:03:40,919 --> 00:03:42,087
I trust you both...

51
00:03:44,381 --> 00:03:45,591
With everything.

52
00:03:50,429 --> 00:03:52,181
Is everything ready?

53
00:03:58,478 --> 00:03:59,438
Are you ready?

54
00:04:02,107 --> 00:04:03,609
Let the show begin.

55
00:04:27,257 --> 00:04:28,425
Where is your wife?

56
00:04:29,301 --> 00:04:32,721
Isn’t this the Velma launch she’s so proud of?

57
00:04:33,889 --> 00:04:35,224
Isn’t she going to face me?

58
00:04:37,017 --> 00:04:37,976
Oh no, she’s here.

59
00:04:39,811 --> 00:04:41,063
She’s not hiding from you.

60
00:04:43,357 --> 00:04:44,191
Oh, I know.

61
00:04:44,608 --> 00:04:47,152
She wants to make a grand entrance.

62
00:04:47,653 --> 00:04:49,112
I can let her know you’re here.

63
00:04:49,238 --> 00:04:50,072
Oh no, no.

64
00:04:50,405 --> 00:04:51,198
Stay with me.

65
00:04:51,740 --> 00:04:52,741
Don’t leave.

66
00:04:55,035 --> 00:04:56,245
Can you believe it, Mama?

67
00:04:56,578 --> 00:04:58,914
All of this just to prove she can get back on her feet.

68
00:05:00,249 --> 00:05:00,999
Sure.

69
00:05:01,583 --> 00:05:02,167
I know.

70
00:05:08,715 --> 00:05:10,217
[SHARI] Okay.

71
00:05:10,801 --> 00:05:12,928
They must never realize you’re still alive.

72
00:05:15,013 --> 00:05:20,269
If we pull this off, justice won’t just be
served for my sister’s death,

73
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:25,107
but for all the women your husband has wronged.

74
00:05:27,234 --> 00:05:29,111
And that includes you, Miss Velma.

75
00:05:34,408 --> 00:05:35,866
[REPORTER] Oh, hi Miss Cristalle Belo!

76
00:05:35,867 --> 00:05:39,120
Are you not threatened by the launch
of Miss Velma Imperial's brand?

77
00:05:39,121 --> 00:05:40,538
No! Not at all.

78
00:05:40,539 --> 00:05:43,207
In the beauty industry, we're all friends.

79
00:05:43,208 --> 00:05:45,418
Ariella, what are you wearing tonight?

80
00:05:45,419 --> 00:05:47,378
You look absolutely stunning!

81
00:05:47,379 --> 00:05:49,547
I'm actually wearing my confidence,

82
00:05:49,548 --> 00:05:52,342
and my ability to stand up after the fall.

83
00:05:52,634 --> 00:05:57,431
Miss Anna, what do you have to
say about Miss Velma's event?

84
00:05:57,931 --> 00:06:00,683
Well, I only have six words for her.

85
00:06:00,684 --> 00:06:03,478
May the best beauty brand win.

86
00:06:03,812 --> 00:06:06,355
In 30 minutes, please turn all the lights off,

87
00:06:06,356 --> 00:06:07,648
the program will start.

88
00:06:07,649 --> 00:06:08,358
Yes, Ma’am.

89
00:06:22,289 --> 00:06:23,248
[METAL DOOR OPENS]

90
00:06:24,499 --> 00:06:26,084
[METAL DOOR OPENS]

91
00:06:28,253 --> 00:06:29,004
[FLIPPING LIGHT BREAKER OFF]

92
00:06:33,842 --> 00:06:37,846
[FLIPPING LIGHT BREAKER OFF]
[PEOPLE GASPING]

93
00:06:39,139 --> 00:06:42,684
[PEOPLE CHATTERING IN SURPRISE]

94
00:06:44,561 --> 00:06:45,479
What happened?

95
00:06:46,521 --> 00:06:47,314
[CLARA] What happened?

96
00:06:47,315 --> 00:06:48,440
It's okay. It's part of it.

97
00:06:49,983 --> 00:06:51,485
The show's about to start.

98
00:06:59,701 --> 00:07:02,913
And to make everyone believe
you’re really dead, Miss V…

99
00:07:10,545 --> 00:07:11,963
It’s to slow your heartbeat down...

100
00:07:13,048 --> 00:07:15,217
In order to make everyone
believe you’re dead.

101
00:07:16,885 --> 00:07:18,720
Just like we planned.

102
00:07:20,514 --> 00:07:21,681
You know what to do.

103
00:07:25,936 --> 00:07:28,105
[VELMA SIGHS ANXIOUSLY] Oh my God,
am I really gonna be doing this?

104
00:07:29,940 --> 00:07:31,316
Are you thinking of backing out?

105
00:07:31,775 --> 00:07:33,193
[VELMA SIGHS ANXIOUSLY] Of course not.

106
00:07:33,819 --> 00:07:37,864
I’m just wondering why I never told the
police about my monstrous husband.

107
00:07:41,243 --> 00:07:44,037
Because you've always loved drama, Miss V.

108
00:07:45,414 --> 00:07:47,916
You know me so very well.

109
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:48,834
[SHARI LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

110
00:07:48,835 --> 00:07:53,839
Well, enjoy your quick visit
to the afterlife.

111
00:08:05,016 --> 00:08:07,144
We'll await your return.

112
00:08:54,232 --> 00:08:57,402
[KRISELDA PLAYING ON SPEAKER] May we request
everyone to please proceed to the gazebo

113
00:08:57,486 --> 00:09:00,989
for the unveiling of Miss Velma's newest baby.

114
00:09:01,531 --> 00:09:02,407
Enjoy!

115
00:09:05,911 --> 00:09:14,044
[PEOPLE CHATTERING IN EXCITEMENT]

116
00:09:24,346 --> 00:09:25,013
Shall we?

117
00:09:31,853 --> 00:09:34,064
[NOREEN GASPS]

118
00:09:40,278 --> 00:09:41,780
[NOREEN SCREAMS IN TERROR]

119
00:09:42,239 --> 00:09:48,744
[NOREEN PANTS]

120
00:09:48,745 --> 00:09:49,954
[WOMAN IN BACKGROUND] Oh my God!
Oh my God!

121
00:09:49,955 --> 00:09:50,413
[WOMAN IN BACKGROUND] Oh my God!

122
00:09:51,081 --> 00:09:52,665
[SHARI] Oh my God, Miss V!

123
00:09:52,666 --> 00:09:53,874
[SHARI PANTS]

124
00:09:53,875 --> 00:09:54,709
You!

125
00:09:55,544 --> 00:09:55,961
Huh?

126
00:09:55,962 --> 00:09:57,837
You killed Miss Velma!

127
00:09:58,129 --> 00:09:59,464
What?!
No!

128
00:10:00,048 --> 00:10:00,715
Velma?

129
00:10:01,174 --> 00:10:01,841
No!

130
00:10:02,384 --> 00:10:03,260
What happened?

131
00:10:04,469 --> 00:10:06,471
[SHARI] I couldn’t have killed her!
I'm not...

132
00:10:06,555 --> 00:10:08,597
- I'm not a murderer!
- [EDDIE] What did you do?!

133
00:10:08,598 --> 00:10:09,558
Velma!

134
00:10:10,058 --> 00:10:11,517
[SHARI] I’m not a murderer!

135
00:10:11,518 --> 00:10:13,228
I could never kill Miss Velma!

136
00:10:14,062 --> 00:10:16,565
Sir Eddie, I didn’t do this to Miss Velma.

137
00:10:17,274 --> 00:10:18,108
Sir Eddie!

138
00:10:18,109 --> 00:10:19,734
Sir Eddie, please believe me!

139
00:10:19,901 --> 00:10:21,026
I’m not a murderer!

140
00:10:21,027 --> 00:10:22,529
I'm not a freaking criminal!

141
00:10:22,737 --> 00:10:24,281
I'm not a criminal!

142
00:10:25,365 --> 00:10:26,533
[EDDIE] You did this!

143
00:10:27,826 --> 00:10:29,369
You’re the only one with a motive!

144
00:10:30,203 --> 00:10:32,372
You held the biggest grudge against her.

145
00:10:32,664 --> 00:10:35,000
The fights you had were terrible,
and now this?!

146
00:10:35,208 --> 00:10:35,709
[SHARI] No, no-

147
00:10:35,710 --> 00:10:39,211
- What did you do?!
- No, Sir Eddie! I did not kill Miss Velma.

148
00:10:39,212 --> 00:10:42,090
I did not kill Miss Velma, Sir Eddie!

149
00:10:42,340 --> 00:10:45,217
I admit I held a grudge against Miss Velma...

150
00:10:45,218 --> 00:10:47,928
We always fought—
But I could never kill her!

151
00:10:47,929 --> 00:10:51,140
I’m not a criminal,
I’m not a freaking criminal!

152
00:10:51,141 --> 00:10:53,268
Then how can you explain this, Shari?!

153
00:10:54,352 --> 00:10:58,732
In case you forgot, you threatened Miss V!

154
00:11:00,233 --> 00:11:02,277
Die, Velma!

155
00:11:02,694 --> 00:11:03,986
That's all I'm going to say.

156
00:11:03,987 --> 00:11:06,990
Die, Velma! Die!

157
00:11:07,449 --> 00:11:08,490
You know?

158
00:11:08,491 --> 00:11:10,034
- I'm the queen.
- Stop it.

159
00:11:10,035 --> 00:11:13,287
The true queen of Velma Beauty, so-

160
00:11:13,288 --> 00:11:14,413
Hi.

161
00:11:14,414 --> 00:11:15,457
Remember me?

162
00:11:19,127 --> 00:11:23,214
You threatened to kill her if she didn’t
hand over Velma Beauty to you, remember?!

163
00:11:23,715 --> 00:11:24,882
- Right?
- [SHARI PANTS ANXIOUSLY] No!

164
00:11:24,883 --> 00:11:26,051
No, no, no, no!

165
00:11:26,092 --> 00:11:28,385
Can someone get this girl out of my sight?!

166
00:11:28,386 --> 00:11:30,138
[SHARI] No! I'm not a criminal!

167
00:11:30,305 --> 00:11:31,473
I'm not a criminal!

168
00:11:32,015 --> 00:11:32,641
[SHARI] No!

169
00:11:32,641 --> 00:11:33,558
I did not kill Miss Velma!

170
00:11:33,559 --> 00:11:36,436
Why are you just standing there?!

171
00:11:37,187 --> 00:11:38,688
Quit taking pictures!

172
00:11:39,230 --> 00:11:39,856
[EDDIE SIGHS SHARPLY]

173
00:11:40,023 --> 00:11:41,483
Why are you taking pictures?!

174
00:11:41,858 --> 00:11:43,360
The nerve of you people!

175
00:11:43,735 --> 00:11:46,863
Take pictures!
Take this! Take that!

176
00:11:49,407 --> 00:11:52,369
[THUNDER]

177
00:16:00,992 --> 00:16:01,743
[CEDRIC] Boss.

178
00:16:02,702 --> 00:16:03,912
I grabbed it before they could find it.

179
00:16:22,513 --> 00:16:24,890
You're going to stab me in the chest, hmm?

180
00:16:24,891 --> 00:16:25,266
[VELMA GASPS]

181
00:16:25,267 --> 00:16:26,517
You plan on telling everyone?

182
00:16:27,226 --> 00:16:30,354
I'm telling you, before you get the chance to do that,

183
00:16:30,355 --> 00:16:31,731
I will kill you first.

184
00:16:37,904 --> 00:16:39,530
My fingerprints are on that.

185
00:16:40,657 --> 00:16:41,865
You know what to do with that.

186
00:16:41,866 --> 00:16:44,118
No one can ever know I touched that.

187
00:16:45,370 --> 00:16:47,537
I also want you to keep a close eye on the police.

188
00:16:47,538 --> 00:16:48,289
Do you understand?

189
00:16:48,748 --> 00:16:49,374
Okay, Boss.

190
00:16:49,457 --> 00:16:51,167
[EDDIE PANTS ANXIOUSLY] Go ahead.

191
00:16:57,090 --> 00:16:57,924
[EDDIE SOBS]

192
00:16:59,008 --> 00:16:59,842
[EDDIE EXHALES SHARPLY]

193
00:17:11,729 --> 00:17:12,355
Son.

194
00:17:12,689 --> 00:17:14,607
Son, I'm here.

195
00:17:15,233 --> 00:17:16,359
[EDDIE SIGHS SHARPLY]

196
00:17:17,443 --> 00:17:18,528
Ma. [EDDIE SOBS]

197
00:17:23,992 --> 00:17:24,826
I don't...

198
00:17:26,119 --> 00:17:27,078
Understand why.

199
00:17:27,078 --> 00:17:28,037
Why Velma?

200
00:17:28,038 --> 00:17:29,663
Why didn't they kill me instead?

201
00:17:29,664 --> 00:17:31,332
I don't— [EDDIE SNIFFLES]

202
00:17:32,709 --> 00:17:33,418
[EDDIS SIGHS SHARPLY]

203
00:17:33,419 --> 00:17:35,545
Whoever did this will pay.

204
00:17:38,339 --> 00:17:39,173
[EDDIE SIGHS SHARPLY]

205
00:17:43,928 --> 00:17:46,514
I'm gonna have to release
a statement tomorrow, Ma.

206
00:17:48,891 --> 00:17:49,934
I'm going to need your help.

207
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:56,691
I'm going to set up a press conference
before the sun rises, okay?

208
00:17:57,066 --> 00:17:58,109
[EDDIE SIGHS SHARPLY]

209
00:18:08,202 --> 00:18:09,162
- Sir Eddie.
- [EDDIE] What is this?

210
00:18:09,996 --> 00:18:11,914
These are Miss Velma's ashes.

211
00:18:12,415 --> 00:18:13,624
I'm bringing her home to you.

212
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:14,834
[EDDIE SCOFFS ANXIOUSLY] What?

213
00:18:22,467 --> 00:18:23,593
Cremated?

214
00:18:25,219 --> 00:18:26,262
That quickly?

215
00:18:27,638 --> 00:18:30,558
Those are all the documents together
with Miss Velma’s final wishes.

216
00:18:31,601 --> 00:18:34,979
The reason for the immediate
cremation is all explained there.

217
00:18:39,358 --> 00:18:43,321
I guess your wife decided,
a long time ago,

218
00:18:44,864 --> 00:18:47,616
not to entrust you with
the final days of her life.

219
00:18:47,617 --> 00:18:48,993
[EDDIE SCOFFS IN SURPRISE] What?

220
00:18:50,620 --> 00:18:52,080
Why?!

221
00:18:55,083 --> 00:18:56,542
[EDDIE STUTTERS]

222
00:19:12,683 --> 00:19:15,228
[EDDIE PANTS LIGHTLY]

223
00:19:18,898 --> 00:19:21,067
[VELMA] I thought I had moved on from this.

224
00:19:21,234 --> 00:19:23,986
But that gut-wrenching feeling is back.

225
00:19:24,737 --> 00:19:25,738
Did you love her?

226
00:19:26,364 --> 00:19:27,824
Was it a one night stand?

227
00:19:28,491 --> 00:19:31,159
Either way, it is disgusting.

228
00:19:31,160 --> 00:19:34,205
That's why I'm going to ask you one last time.

229
00:19:35,957 --> 00:19:37,291
Did you really do it?

230
00:19:37,708 --> 00:19:39,210
No, I did not.

231
00:19:39,710 --> 00:19:41,294
Tell me the truth!

232
00:19:41,295 --> 00:19:42,421
This is the truth!

233
00:19:42,505 --> 00:19:44,173
Why won't you believe me?

234
00:19:44,966 --> 00:19:47,217
Why won't you just tell me the truth?

235
00:19:47,218 --> 00:19:49,386
You drugged her! You raped her!

236
00:19:49,387 --> 00:19:50,680
You killed her!

237
00:19:50,930 --> 00:19:51,806
You murdered her!

238
00:19:51,807 --> 00:19:52,931
You're a murderer!

239
00:19:52,932 --> 00:19:53,933
That's enough!

240
00:19:54,016 --> 00:19:54,767
I'm done!

241
00:19:55,017 --> 00:19:55,685
It's over!

242
00:19:56,102 --> 00:19:58,103
Keep pestering me and see what happens!

243
00:19:58,104 --> 00:19:59,689
I might just kill you!

244
00:20:06,737 --> 00:20:13,368
[YLORNA GROANING IN PAIN]
[HEART MONITOR BEEPING]

245
00:20:13,369 --> 00:20:18,582
Noreen, please.
Let me out of here, please!

246
00:20:18,583 --> 00:20:22,753
Sir, any news on Eddie Imperial?

247
00:20:23,004 --> 00:20:25,673
We’ve been keeping an eye on Eddie for a while,

248
00:20:26,382 --> 00:20:30,178
and we’re already aware of his
illegal underground businesses.

249
00:20:30,761 --> 00:20:36,309
And according to our latest intel,
Mister Imperial has a new ally.

250
00:20:46,652 --> 00:20:51,364
[REPORTER] Breaking news:
Shari De Jesus has been released from prison.

251
00:20:51,365 --> 00:20:53,534
I’ve been trying to reach Shari,
but she’s not answering.

252
00:20:54,619 --> 00:20:56,328
I can’t believe this is happening.

253
00:20:56,329 --> 00:20:57,705
I’m worried, Noreen.

254
00:20:58,456 --> 00:21:00,166
Shari’s will do a livestream.

255
00:21:09,425 --> 00:21:10,926
Before you can even take me down,

256
00:21:10,927 --> 00:21:13,095
I will kill all of you first!

257
00:21:13,804 --> 00:21:17,600
Ever since Velma died, you
have been acting weird!

258
00:21:17,808 --> 00:21:19,727
You're asking me why I'm like this?

259
00:21:20,853 --> 00:21:22,354
